# RotatingOfferstrip.js — Code Review (Functionality Issues)

## Issues & Solutions

---

### Issue 1: Scroll Logic Does Not Re-Show Bar When Scrolling Up Above 50px (Lines 107–115)

**Lines:** 107–115  
**Code:**
```js
if (currentScroll <= 0) {
    offerBar.classList.remove("hidden");
    document.body.classList.remove('offer-bar-hidden');
} else if (currentScroll > lastScroll && currentScroll > 50) {
    offerBar.classList.add("hidden");
    document.body.classList.add('offer-bar-hidden');
} else if (currentScroll < lastScroll && currentScroll <= 50) {
    offerBar.classList.remove("hidden");
    document.body.classList.remove('offer-bar-hidden');
}
```

**Problem:** The bar is only re-shown when scrolling **up AND** scroll position is ≤ 50px. If the user scrolls down 500px then scrolls back up to 200px, the bar stays hidden. For a "show on scroll up" pattern, the bar should reappear on any upward scroll.

**Solution:** Remove the `&& currentScroll <= 50` restriction:
```js
if (currentScroll <= 0) {
    offerBar.classList.remove("hidden");
    document.body.classList.remove('offer-bar-hidden');
} else if (currentScroll > lastScroll && currentScroll > 50) {
    offerBar.classList.add("hidden");
    document.body.classList.add('offer-bar-hidden');
} else if (currentScroll < lastScroll) {
    offerBar.classList.remove("hidden");
    document.body.classList.remove('offer-bar-hidden');
}
```

