### Issue 2: No Cleanup / Teardown — Memory Leak in SPA (Lines 121–128)

**Lines:** 121–128  
**Code:**
```js
window.addEventListener("scroll", function() { ... });
window.addEventListener("resize", function() { ... });
```

**Problem:** Event listeners are added with anonymous functions and never removed. If this script runs in a Single Page Application where the page/component is destroyed and re-created, orphaned listeners accumulate causing memory leaks and duplicate scroll handling.

**Solution:** Use named functions and expose a destroy method:
```js
const scrollHandler = function() {
    if (!ticking) {
        window.requestAnimationFrame(handleScroll);
        ticking = true;
    }
};
const resizeHandler = function() {
    clearTimeout(resizeTimer);
    resizeTimer = setTimeout(updateOfferBarHeight, 250);
};
window.addEventListener("scroll", scrollHandler);
window.addEventListener("resize", resizeHandler);

window.__offerRotatorDestroy = function() {
    window.removeEventListener("scroll", scrollHandler);
    window.removeEventListener("resize", resizeHandler);
    offerBar.remove();
    document.body.classList.remove('has-offer-bar', 'offer-bar-hidden');
};
```

