### Issue 3: `document.body` Null Reference Crash (Line 91)

**Line:** 91  
**Code:**
```js
document.body.classList.add('has-offer-bar');
```

**Problem:** Line 89 uses `document.body || document.documentElement` as a fallback, acknowledging that `document.body` could be `null` (e.g., if the script runs in `<head>` before the body exists). But line 91 accesses `document.body.classList` directly — this will throw a `TypeError` if `document.body` is indeed `null`.

**Solution:** Guard the call or ensure the script only runs after the DOM is ready:
```js
// Option A: Guard
if (document.body) {
    document.body.classList.add('has-offer-bar');
}

// Option B: Wrap entire IIFE in DOMContentLoaded
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() { ... });
```

