### Issue 4: Header Position Not Restored on Scroll Up (Lines 35–42)

**Lines:** 35–42  
**Code:**
```css
body.has-offer-bar .headerv2.fixed-top,
body.has-offer-bar .headerv2 {
    top: var(--offer-bar-height, 32px) !important;
}

body.has-offer-bar.offer-bar-hidden .headerv2.fixed-top,
body.has-offer-bar.offer-bar-hidden .headerv2 {
    top: 0 !important;
}
```

**Problem:** Combined with Issue 1 — since the bar doesn't re-show on scroll up above 50px, the `offer-bar-hidden` class stays on the body. This means `.headerv2` stays at `top: 0` even when the offer bar should be visible again, causing the header and offer bar to overlap.

**Solution:** Fixing Issue 1 (the scroll logic) resolves this automatically. The header's `top` value will correctly toggle as the bar shows/hides.

